      "is_answer_order_important": false,
      "stimulus_html": "",
      "stem_html": "<p>The amino acid tyrosine is biologically degraded by a series of steps that include the following transformations:</p>\n<img src=\"https://exercises.openstax.org/rails/active_storage/blobs/proxy/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaHBBdUlaIiwiZXhwIjpudWxsLCJwdXIiOiJibG9iX2lkIn19--be2b0dce03499957fb60e7e266bda79e0d33d98d/OChem_29_EC_009.jpg\" alt=\"Tyrosine is degraded to maleoylacetoacetate and then to fumaroylacetoacetate, and acetoacetate and fumarate with acetoacetate forming coenzyme A.\">\n<p>The double-bond isomerization of maleoylacetoacetate to fumaroylacetoacetate is catalyzed by practically any nucleophile, <b>:</b>Nu<sup>–</sup>. Propose a mechanism.</p>",
